                  <msContents>
                     <summary>Treatise arguing for the right of ʻAlī to be regarded as the
								Imām and successor of the prophet Muḥammad. Although neither title
								nor author are included in the text, this work can be identified as
								<title key="work_23282">Fawz al-najāt</title> attributed to Muʻizz al-Dīn
								Ardistānī. Dedicated to <persName role="pat" key="viaf_44546161">ʻAbd Allāh Quṭb Shāh</persName> (r. 1611-72) the work was
								completed in 1058/1648-9. 
                     </summary>
                     <msItem class="https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2010112937 https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85121391">
                        <locus from="1v" to="233v">ff. 1v-233v</locus>
                        <author key="person_f8384">
                           <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muʻizz al-Dīn
										Ardistānī</persName>
                           <persName xml:lang="fa">معز الدین اردستانی</persName>
                        </author>
                        <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23282">Fawz al-najāt</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23282">فوز النجات</title>
                        <note>Folios 232-3 are in a different hand. </note>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
										the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f049r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 49</ref>. 
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                        <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                        <filiation>For another copy in the British Library, see Or. 1294
									(Rieu 1879-83, p. 32). </filiation>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
